The '''Consultative Council on National Health Insurance''' was established under the [[Ministry of Health Act 1919]] along with the National Health Insurance Joint Committee.
Sir [[Thomas Neill (insurance executive)|Thomas Neill]] was chair until 1924 and was knighted for his services in the [[1920 New Year Honours]] <ref>{{London Gazette |issue=31712 |date=30 December 1919 |page=3 |supp=y}}</ref> In 1934 the chair was Mr. J. W. Shaw, of the [[Order of Druids]] Friendly Society.<ref>{{cite news|title=Oral answers to questions|url=http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/commons/1934/dec/13/consultative-council-on-national-health|accessdate=10 November 2016|publisher=Hansard|date=13 December 1934}}</ref>
Records of the Councils and their subcommittees are held in the National Archives.<ref>{{cite web|title=Records of the National Health Insurance Joint Committee, Commissions, and Consultative Council|url=http://discovery.nationalarchives.gov.uk/details/r/C984|website=The National Archives|accessdate=10 November 2016}}</ref>
