{{Expand Swedish|date=January 2011|Gamla riksarkivet}} {{Infobox building |image=Gamla riksarkivet.jpg |caption=Gamla Riksarkivet |name=Gamla Riksarkivet |location_town=[[Stockholm]] |location_country=[[Sweden]] |architect=Axel F. Nyström |client= |engineer= |construction_start_date=1877 |completion_date=1890 |date_demolished= |cost= |structural_system= |style= }}
{{see also|Sweden during the late 19th century}}
'''Gamla Riksarkivet''' (Old National Archives) is a building at Arkivgatan 3 on [[Riddarholmen]] in [[Stockholm]], [[Sweden]]. [[National Archives of Sweden|Riksarkivet]], the Swedish National Archives, were located in the building until 1968.
The 19th century [[Brick Romanesque]] architecture of the building is alluding to the medieval history of Riddarholmen. The plan of the building is, however, typical for public buildings of its era, the grand style central portion clearly articulated in the façade together with the huge windows of the reading-room. The building is connected to the [[Stenbock Palace]] where the archive was once started in 1863. It is also similar in style to the [[Norstedt Building]] located just north of it.<ref name="guide-136">{{cite book | title = Guide till Stockholms arkitektur | edition = 2nd | year = 1999 | author = Mårtelius, Johan | publisher = Arkitektur Förlag AB | location = Stockholm | isbn = 91-86050-41-9 | chapter = Norra innerstaden | page = 136 }}</ref>
